{"id":"9899","name":"Shortcut Downgrader","tagline":"Download iOS 15/16 shortcuts on iOS 14","icon":"ios14 c4292093695 g61440","latest":"34771","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>OS</th>\n<th>Compatibility</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>macOS</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>iOS 15 or higher</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>iOS 14 or lower</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>If you see a spinning indicator when downloading a shortcut on iOS 14, it means that the shortcut is for iOS 15 or later. This shortcut tries to create an iOS 14-compatible version.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Screenshot of spinning indicator\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/4apoW5E.png\"></p>\n<ol>\n<li>When you see a spinning indicator,</li>\n<li>Tap <em>Share</em> and run <em>Shortcut Downgrader</em>.</li>\n<li>In the next screen, delete <strong>.shortcut</strong> from the name.</li>\n<li>Scroll down and tap <em>Add</em>. Done.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img alt=\"Screenshot for renaming\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/QGJ1mI4.png\"></p>\n<h2>Notes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>This shortcut does not work on iOS 15 or later.</li>\n<li>You can also copy an iCloud link and run the shortcut directly.</li>\n<li>Shortcuts containing newer actions may not run even after downgrading.</li>\n<li>For technical details: <a href=\"https://redd.it/opak23/\">https://redd.it/opak23/</a></li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.2.1 - Sept. 1, 2022, 10:20 a.m.</strong></p><p>2022-09-01<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;â€¢ Bug fix in handling Get File and Save File actions</p>"}